# Nextcloud Homelab: Self-Hosted Google Photos & Drive Replacement

A full documentation of my process building a self-hosted Nextcloud server on repurposed hardware — covering hardware failures, network troubleshooting, and the final working setup.

---

## Project Goal

Replace Google Photos and Google Drive with a private, self-hosted alternative using Nextcloud running on an old laptop. The aim was full control over personal files and photos, with no third-party cloud involved.

**Planned storage layout:**
- ~300GB allocated to Nextcloud (files and photos)
- 1TB+ reserved for Jellyfin (media server, future phase)

