## Installation Overview

### Step 1: Create a Bootable USB

Downloaded Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS from the official Ubuntu website. Used Balena Etcher to flash the ISO onto a USB drive. When plugged into Windows, the drive appeared as two partitions — this is normal behavior and requires no formatting.

### Step 2: Prepare the Laptop for Ubuntu

- Plugged the USB into the Vivobook
- Entered BIOS by pressing F2 on startup
- Set USB as the first boot priority
- Saved and exited — the Ubuntu Server installer launched

### Step 3: Ubuntu Installer Configuration

- Selected language and keyboard layout
- Configured network interface
- Chose full disk installation (no dual boot)
- Confirmed and started the installation

